==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embryonic
<hw>Em`bry*on"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to an embryo; embryonal; rudimentary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Embryonic sac</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>Embryonic vesicle</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>the
vesicle within which the embryo is developed in the ovule; -- sometimes
called also <altname>amnios sac</altname>, and <altname>embryonal
sac</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embryoniferous</ent>⟦br⟧
